            <div type="translation"><note>After Synaxarion for 12 Nahase</note>
                <ab>On this day is celebrated the festival of the glorious Archangel Michael, for on this day he
                    appeared unto the righteous Constantine above the city of Rome, and gave him power over
                    all his enemies, and the emperor conquered them, and his kingdom became strong. And he
                    destroyed the houses of idols, and built churches, and decorated them with every kind of
                    decoration. For this reason our Fathers, the doctors of the Church, have commanded us to
                    celebrate the festival of the glorious angel, Michael the archangel, on the twenty-second (?)
                    day of this month</ab></div>
